<title>USA: Xircom in pact with networking companies.</title>
<headline>Xircom in pact with networking companies.</headline>
<dateline>THOUSAND OAKS, Calif. 1997-07-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Xircom Inc on Tuesday said it entered into a marketing agreement with several networking companies under which North American customers will receive a free modem when they buy remote access equipment.</p>
<p>Xircom said it will give a free CreditCard Ethernet 10/100+Modem 56 to customers who purchase qualifying remote access equipment from Ascend Communications Inc, Bay Networks Inc or Cisco Systems Inc.</p>
<p>Xircom's CreditCard Ethernet 10/100+Modem 56 combines a network adapter and 56K modem in a single PC Card.</p>
<p>Xircm said the modem regularly sells at retail for about $379.</p>
<p>Financial details of agreements were not disclosed.</p>
